# Product Development Requirement (PDR)
## Modern UI Component Library - "ZenUI"

---

**Document Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** January 31, 2026  
**Status:** Draft  
**Owner:** Development Team  
**Stakeholders:** Frontend Developers, Design Team, Open Source Community

---

## 1. Executive Summary

### 1.1 Product Vision
ZenUI is a modern, framework-agnostic UI component library designed to provide developers with beautiful, accessible, and highly customizable components. Inspired by the philosophy of shadcn/ui and Magic UI, ZenUI focuses on giving developers full ownership of their code while maintaining exceptional design quality and developer experience.

### 1.2 Product Positioning
- **Primary Inspiration:** shadcn/ui (copy-paste approach), Magic UI (premium animations)
- **Target Frameworks:** React, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt
- **Unique Value Proposition:** World-class UI design with premium animations, full code ownership, zero runtime dependencies, and top-tier aesthetic quality that rivals the best design agencies

### 1.3 Success Metrics
- **Adoption:** 10K+ GitHub stars in first year
- **Usage:** 50K+ monthly npm downloads
- **Community:** 100+ community-contributed components
- **Documentation:** 95%+ positive feedback on docs quality
- **Performance:** All components score 95+ on Lighthouse

---

## 2. Market Analysis

### 2.1 Competitive Landscape

| Product | Approach | Strengths | Gaps |
|---------|----------|-----------|------|
| shadcn/ui | Copy-paste components | Full ownership, customizable | React-only, limited animations |
| Magic UI | Premium animated components | Beautiful animations | Paid, limited customization |
| Chakra UI | NPM package | Complete ecosystem | Bundle size, less control |
| Material UI | NPM package | Comprehensive, mature | Heavy, opinionated |
| Radix UI | Headless primitives | Accessibility-first | Requires styling effort |

### 2.2 Market Opportunity
- Growing demand for customizable component libraries
- Shift toward "copy-paste" philosophy for better control
- Need for premium animations without vendor lock-in
- Multi-framework support increasingly important
- Developer preference for lightweight, tree-shakeable solutions

### 2.3 Target Audience

#### Primary Users
1. **Senior Frontend Developers**
   - Need full control over component implementation
   - Value code quality and customization
   - Building production applications

2. **Startup Teams**
   - Need rapid development without sacrificing quality
   - Want premium UI without high costs
   - Require flexibility to customize

3. **Design Engineers**
   - Focus on micro-interactions and animations
   - Need components that match design vision
   - Value aesthetic excellence

#### Secondary Users
- Freelance developers building client projects
- Open source maintainers
- Technical content creators
- Design system teams

---

## 3. Product Requirements

### 3.1 Core Philosophy

#### Design Principles
1. **Code Ownership:** Users own 100% of component code
2. **Zero Runtime Deps:** No proprietary runtime dependencies
3. **Framework Support:** React, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt with equal quality
4. **World-Class Design:** UI quality that matches top design agencies (Vercel, Linear, Stripe)
5. **Accessibility First:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
6. **Performance Obsessed:** Minimal bundle impact
7. **Premium Aesthetics:** Every component should WOW users at first glance
8. **Fully Customizable:** Easy to modify and extend
9. **Pixel Perfect:** Attention to micro-details, spacing, typography, and interactions

#### Technical Principles
1. **TypeScript First:** Full type safety
2. **Composable:** Small, focused components
3. **Tree-Shakeable:** Import only what you need
4. **Modern Standards:** Latest web platform features
5. **Progressive Enhancement:** Works without JavaScript where possible

### 3.2 Component Categories

#### 3.2.1 Foundation Components (Phase 1)
**Priority: Critical**

> [!NOTE]
> All components must have world-class UI design quality. Think: "What would a top UI design engineer at Vercel create?" Every hover state, transition, and spacing detail matters.

| Component | Description | Complexity | Dependencies | Design Notes |
|-----------|-------------|------------|--------------|-------------|
| Button | Multiple variants, sizes, states with premium hover effects | Low | None | Magnetic hover, ripple effects, gradient options, smooth scale on press |
| Input | Text, password, email, number with floating labels | Medium | None | Smooth focus states, animated borders, floating label animation |
| Textarea | Multi-line text input with auto-resize | Low | None | Elegant scrollbar, character count animation, resize handle |
| Select | Dropdown selection with search | Medium | Floating UI | Smooth open/close animation, keyboard navigation, search highlight |
| Checkbox | Boolean selection with smooth animations | Low | None | Checkmark draw animation, indeterminate state, ripple effect |
| Radio | Single selection with ripple effect | Low | None | Smooth selection animation, scale feedback, group coordination |
| Switch | Toggle control with spring animation | Low | None | iOS-style smooth transition, haptic-like feedback, thumb shadow |
| Label | Form labels with accessibility | Low | None | Subtle animations on focus, proper spacing, color transitions |
| Badge | Status indicators with variants | Low | None | Dot pulse animation, gradient options, subtle glow effects |
| Avatar | User profile images with fallback | Low | None | Smooth loading transition, status indicator pulse, border glow |

