#### 3.2.7 Glassmorphic Components (Phase 2)
**Priority: High (Design Differentiator)**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These components are a key differentiator. UI quality must match or exceed premium design agencies like Vercel, Linear, and Stripe. Every detail matters: blur intensity, border subtlety, shadow depth, and hover transitions.

| Component | Description | Complexity | Dependencies | Design Notes |
|-----------|-------------|------------|--------------|--------------|
| Glass Card | Frosted glass card with backdrop blur | Medium | None | Perfect 12-16px blur, subtle white/10% border, soft shadow, gradient overlay |
| Glass Modal | Modal with glassmorphic background | High | Portal | Smooth backdrop blur animation, elegant multi-layer shadows, border glow |
| Glass Navigation | Navbar with glass effect | Medium | None | Sticky blur effect, smooth scroll transitions, adaptive opacity |
| Glass Sidebar | Sidebar with frosted glass | Medium | None | Adaptive blur based on background content, smooth slide animation |
| Glass Panel | Floating panel with glass effect | Low | None | Customizable blur intensity (8-20px), border shine, depth shadows |
| Glass Button | Button with glassmorphism | Low | None | Hover state enhances blur + brightness, ripple effect, magnetic cursor |
| Glass Input | Input field with glass background | Medium | None | Focus state with glow effect, smooth border animation, floating label |
| Glass Dropdown | Dropdown with frosted glass | High | Floating UI | Smooth blur animation on open, stagger menu items, backdrop filter |

**Glassmorphic Design Standards:**
- **Backdrop Blur:** 12-16px for cards, 20-24px for modals
- **Background:** `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)` dark mode, `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7)` light mode
- **Border:** 1px solid with `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)` for subtle definition
- **Shadow:** Multi-layer shadows for depth (0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1))
- **Hover States:** Increase blur by 2-4px, brighten background by 5%
- **Performance:** Use `will-change: backdrop-filter` sparingly, optimize for 60fps

