#### 3.3.5 CLI Tool Architecture

**Installation Flow:**
```bash
# Initialize project
npx zenui-cli init

# Add individual components
npx zenui-cli add button
npx zenui-cli add dialog

# Add multiple components
npx zenui-cli add button dialog card

# Add all components
npx zenui-cli add --all

# Update components
npx zenui-cli update button

# List available components
npx zenui-cli list

# Search components
npx zenui-cli search modal
```

**CLI Features:**
1. **Framework Detection:** Auto-detect React/Vue/Next/Nuxt
2. **Dependency Management:** Install required peer dependencies
3. **Configuration:** Setup Tailwind, TypeScript configs
4. **Customization:** Allow variant selection during install
5. **Updates:** Track and update component versions
6. **Theming:** Apply pre-built themes

### 3.4 Accessibility Requirements

#### 3.4.1 Standards Compliance
- **WCAG 2.1 Level AA:** Minimum compliance
- **ARIA 1.2:** Proper ARIA attributes
- **Keyboard Navigation:** Full keyboard support
- **Screen Reader:** Tested with NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver
- **Focus Management:** Visible focus indicators

#### 3.4.2 Accessibility Checklist (Per Component)
- [ ] Semantic HTML elements
- [ ] Proper ARIA roles and attributes
- [ ] Keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Space, Escape, Arrows)
- [ ] Focus management and focus trapping (modals)
- [ ] Screen reader announcements
- [ ] Color contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum)
- [ ] Focus visible indicators
- [ ] Reduced motion support
- [ ] Touch target sizes (44x44px minimum)
- [ ] Error messages and validation feedback

#### 3.4.3 Testing Requirements
- Automated testing with axe-core
- Manual testing with screen readers
- Keyboard-only navigation testing
- Color contrast validation
- Accessibility audit in CI/CD

### 3.5 Performance Requirements

#### 3.5.1 Bundle Size Targets
| Metric | Target | Maximum |
|--------|--------|---------|
| Single component | < 5KB | 10KB |
| Component + deps | < 15KB | 25KB |
| Full library (tree-shaken) | < 50KB | 100KB |
| CSS (minified) | < 20KB | 40KB |

#### 3.5.2 Runtime Performance
- **First Contentful Paint:** < 1.5s
- **Time to Interactive:** < 3.5s
- **Component Mount:** < 16ms (60fps)
- **Animation Frame Rate:** 60fps minimum
- **Memory Usage:** < 10MB per component

#### 3.5.3 Optimization Strategies
1. **Code Splitting:** Each component is independently importable
2. **Tree Shaking:** ES modules for optimal tree-shaking
3. **Lazy Loading:** Support for dynamic imports
4. **CSS Optimization:** PurgeCSS for unused styles
5. **Image Optimization:** WebP, AVIF support
6. **Animation Performance:** GPU-accelerated transforms
7. **Virtualization:** For large lists/tables

