## 4. User Experience Requirements

### 4.1 Component Interaction Patterns

#### 4.1.1 Micro-interactions
- Hover states with smooth transitions
- Click feedback (scale, color change)
- Loading states with spinners/skeletons
- Success/error animations
- Drag and drop feedback

#### 4.1.2 Animation Guidelines
- **Duration:** 150-300ms for most interactions
- **Easing:** Ease-out for entrances, ease-in for exits
- **Respect Motion Preferences:** `prefers-reduced-motion`
- **Performance:** Use transform and opacity only
- **Purposeful:** Animations should enhance UX, not distract

### 4.2 Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px), 2xl (1536px)
- Touch-friendly targets (44x44px minimum)
- Adaptive layouts
- Responsive typography

### 4.3 Form Validation
- Real-time validation
- Clear error messages
- Inline error display
- Success states
- Accessible error announcements

---

## 5. Quality Assurance

### 5.1 Testing Strategy

#### 5.1.1 Unit Testing
- **Framework:** Vitest
- **Coverage Target:** 80% minimum
- **Test Cases:**
  - Component rendering
  - Prop validation
  - Event handling
  - State management
  - Edge cases

#### 5.1.2 Integration Testing
- **Framework:** Testing Library
- **Focus:**
  - User interactions
  - Form submissions
  - Navigation flows
  - Accessibility

#### 5.1.3 E2E Testing
- **Framework:** Playwright
- **Scenarios:**
  - Critical user paths
  - Cross-browser compatibility
  - Responsive behavior
  - Performance benchmarks

#### 5.1.4 Visual Regression Testing
- **Framework:** Chromatic or Percy
- **Coverage:** All component variants

### 5.2 Browser Support
| Browser | Minimum Version |
|---------|----------------|
| Chrome | Last 2 versions |
| Firefox | Last 2 versions |
| Safari | Last 2 versions |
| Edge | Last 2 versions |
| Mobile Safari | iOS 14+ |
| Chrome Mobile | Last 2 versions |

### 5.3 Code Quality
