## 8. Technical Specifications

### 8.1 Component API Design

#### 8.1.1 Prop Naming Conventions
- Use camelCase for props
- Boolean props: `isOpen`, `isDisabled`, `hasError`
- Event handlers: `onClick`, `onClose`, `onChange`
- Variants: `variant`, `size`, `color`
- Composition: `asChild` for polymorphism

#### 8.1.2 Event Handling
```typescript
// Consistent event signatures
type ClickHandler = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void
type ChangeHandler = (value: string) => void
type SubmitHandler = (data: FormData) => void | Promise<void>
```

#### 8.1.3 Ref Forwarding
- All interactive components forward refs
- Expose imperative handles where appropriate
- Type-safe ref types

### 8.2 Animation Specifications

#### 8.2.1 Framer Motion Variants
```typescript
// Standard animation variants
const fadeIn = {
  initial: { opacity: 0 },
  animate: { opacity: 1 },
  exit: { opacity: 0 },
}

const slideUp = {
  initial: { y: 20, opacity: 0 },
  animate: { y: 0, opacity: 1 },
  exit: { y: -20, opacity: 0 },
}

const scaleIn = {
  initial: { scale: 0.95, opacity: 0 },
  animate: { scale: 1, opacity: 1 },
  exit: { scale: 0.95, opacity: 0 },
}
```

#### 8.2.2 CSS Animations
```css
/* Tailwind animation utilities */
@keyframes shimmer {
  0% { transform: translateX(-100%); }
  100% { transform: translateX(100%); }
}

@keyframes pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
  50% { opacity: 0.5; }
}

@keyframes spin {
  from { transform: rotate(0deg); }
  to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}
```

### 8.3 Accessibility Implementation

#### 8.3.1 Focus Management
```typescript
// Focus trap for modals
import { useFocusTrap } from '@zenui/core'

const Dialog = () => {
  const trapRef = useFocusTrap({ active: isOpen })
  
  return (
    <div ref={trapRef} role="dialog" aria-modal="true">
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

#### 8.3.2 ARIA Patterns
- Follow WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices Guide
- Implement proper roles, states, and properties
- Live regions for dynamic content
- Descriptive labels and descriptions

### 8.4 Internationalization (i18n)

#### 8.4.1 Text Content
- All user-facing text externalized
- Support for RTL languages
- Date/time formatting
- Number formatting

#### 8.4.2 Implementation
```typescript
// i18n support
const Button = ({ children, locale = 'en' }) => {
  const t = useTranslation(locale)
  
  return (
    <button aria-label={t('button.label')}>
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}
```

